cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a memory-augmented neural network framework for semantic segmentation in medical imaging, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the issue of domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves contextual embeddings, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.MM and cs.NE.
